<h2 id="common-questions">Common Questions</h2>

<h3 id="q-isnt-this-coupling-services-together">Q: “Isn’t this coupling services together?”</h3>

<p><strong>A: No.</strong> Services are coupled at <strong>build time</strong> (good) but independent at <strong>runtime</strong> (critical).</p>
<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Build time: 
  services depend on packages ✅

Runtime:
  auth-service → separate container
  sources-service → separate container
  scraper-service → separate container
  All deploy independently ✅
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="q-what-if-i-need-to-change-a-package">Q: “What if I need to change a package?”</h3>

<p><strong>A: Version it.</strong></p>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="c"># Make breaking change in @radarkit/logger</span>
<span class="nb">cd </span>packages/logger
<span class="c"># Update to 2.0.0</span>

<span class="c"># Services opt-in when ready</span>
<span class="c"># auth-service uses logger@2.0.0</span>
<span class="c"># sources-service still on logger@1.0.0</span>
<span class="c"># No forced migration</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="q-how-do-i-test-packages">Q: “How do I test packages?”</h3>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="c"># Test package in isolation</span>
<span class="nb">cd </span>packages/logger
npm <span class="nb">test</span>

<span class="c"># Test service with package</span>
<span class="nb">cd </span>services/auth-service
npm <span class="nb">test</span>  <span class="c"># Uses @radarkit/logger via symlink</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

